Gospel singer, Prince Gozie Okeke, popularly known for his song ‘Akanchawa’, has been gifted a brand new Lexus SUV by Rev. Father Ejike Mbaka of the Adoration Ministry, Enugu, to mark the New Year. The singer, who could not contain his joy, took to his Instagram page to share a video of his brand new ride while showering love on the clergyman. In the video, Gozie is seen seated with Fr Mbaka beside him on the passenger side while he (Father Mbaka) danced to a gospel song. Read Also: Mbaka raises alarm over another DSS invitation   How Nollywood can go global, by BBN Leo Dasilva     Tiwa Savage’s ex-husband TeeBill becomes father again     My ex-girlfriend had no twins for me, says Harrysong   Okeke on the other hand had an absolutely surprised countenance as he placed his hands on his head and later folded his arms still looking dazed. - Advertisement - “All I have to say is thank you Jesus, My father in the Lord Rev Fr. Ejike Mbaka U will hear from me soon. “May God keep you for me in the name of Jesus Christ Amen. I love you with passion, ” Gozie captioned the video. Meanwhile, the person behind the video making could be heard saying: “This is the car, the new car. This is the car as a New Year gift from Rev. Fr Mbaka to Gozie Okeke.” Smitten by the automobile, the man added: “Look at this car!”